  "keyFeatures": [
    "Minimal attack surface: no shell, no package manager, no OS utilities",
    "Very small image sizes (static image ~2 MiB vs Alpine ~5 MiB vs Debian ~124 MiB)",
    "Multi-architecture support (amd64, arm64, arm, s390x, ppc64le, riscv64)",
    "Images signed with cosign for supply chain security",
    "Language-specific images for Go, Java, Python, Node.js, Rust, C/C++",
    "Debug variants with busybox shell for troubleshooting",
    "Automatic CVE tracking via Debian upstream releases",
    "Works with Docker multi-stage builds and Bazel rules_oci"
